title: Devonta Freeman juked his way to the first touchdown of Super Bowl 51
text: Rec Devonta Freeman got the Atlanta Falcons first on the board in Super Bowl LI when Matt Ryan handed him the ball off, putting the Falcons up 7-0. Freeman had tons of space, and there was no question that he was going to get in. He even ended it with a beautifully done dive. The Falcons have played pretty well on both sides of the ball, and itâ€™s going to be a confidence booster moving forward playing with a lead, even if it is still early. In this Storystream
